                    <comment id="12366427" author="hossman" created="Wed, 15 Feb 2006 11:24:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Class with utility function, and main that calls it on an FSDirectory.  Also test cases for the utility function using a RAMDirectory&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12366436" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Wed, 15 Feb 2006 14:02:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good!  Should this be in the index package?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You could even optionally reconstruct the boost if you wanted to (to the precision allowed by the 8 bit float at least) by using the original Similarity to calculate what the lengthNorm is alone, and comparing against the actual norm.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12375177" author="hossman" created="Thu, 20 Apr 2006 02:23:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI: I picked the package to match the other classes in contrib/miscellaneous ... I don&apos;t think it matters very much what package it lives in.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As for reconstructing the boost: It&apos;s possible, but this met my needs and I&apos;ve got some bigger things to worry about at the moment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
